## Known Issues
- **Apostrophe in project path:** The path "Claude's Home" contains an apostrophe which can cause glob/search failures in subagents. When delegating file searches to subagents, ensure paths are properly quoted or escaped.

See `memory/` for detailed profiles and context.

## Dashboard
- **Run with:** `node serve.js` (from project root) — opens at `http://localhost:3000/dashboard/`
- TASKS.md and memory files auto-load via HTTP fetch on page load
- Tasks poll every 2s for changes — edits via Claude Code appear automatically

### Dashboard Architecture
- `dashboard/js/main.js` — entry point, imports all modules, config loading
- `dashboard/js/tasks-parser.js` — parses TASKS.md markdown into structured data
- `dashboard/js/tasks-board.js` — board view rendering, drag-drop, inline card editing
- `dashboard/js/tasks-list.js` — list view rendering
- `dashboard/js/memory-renderer.js` — memory tab rendering (grouped sidebar nav, overview, files, directories)
- `dashboard/js/memory-parser.js` — parses memory markdown files (fields, tables, sections)
- `dashboard/js/memory-modal.js` — modal CRUD for people/projects pages
- `dashboard/js/inline-edit.js` — inline editing for context page (fields, table cells, section lines)
- `dashboard/js/http-loader.js` — HTTP fetch/save fallback (httpSave, loadMemoryViaHttp)
- `dashboard/js/state.js` — shared state, tab switching, status bar
- `dashboard/js/persistence.js` — IndexedDB handle storage for FileSystem API
- `dashboard/js/overview.js` — overview tab widgets
- `dashboard/js/theme.js` — dark/light theme toggle (dark is the default theme)
- `dashboard/styles/` — base.css, tasks.css, memory.css, modal.css, overview.css, misc.css, global-memory.css
- `dashboard/styles/base.css` — design-token system: all colors/spacing/radius/type/shadow values are CSS custom properties (`--surface-0..4`, `--status-*`, `--priority-*`, `--space-*`, `--text-*`); dark tokens live in `:root`, light overrides in `[data-theme="light"]`. Restyle via tokens, not hardcoded values.
- `serve.js` — Node.js dev server with `/api/save` (POST) and `/api/memory-manifest` (GET); port via `PORT` env or first CLI arg (default 3000)
- UI conventions: semantic status colors (todo=blue, done=green, high-priority=red, in-progress=terracotta); accent reserved for interactive elements; focus rings via `--focus-ring` box-shadow; CSS classes referenced from JS (e.g. `inline-edit-input`, `priority-legend`, `gm-*`) are load-bearing — rename in both places or not at all

### Task Priority System
- Priorities: `low` (blue), `medium` (yellow), `high` (red) — default is `medium`
- Stored in TASKS.md HTML comments: `<\!-- created:2026-02-22 priority:medium -->`
- Board shows clickable priority dots — click cycles low → medium → high
- Notes use em-dash separator: `**Title** — note text`
